## 1. Strategic Thesis

primepm is a project portfolio management (PPM) tool with **baseline integrity, earned value tracking, and governance discipline built in by default — not bolted on**.

The market is saturated with PM tools that let teams silently move goalposts, mask schedule slip, and avoid hard decisions. Incumbents (Planview, Clarity, Primavera, ServiceNow SPM) have these features in name but rarely enforce them. primepm's differentiation is the **enforcement**, not the feature inventory.

**Target buyer:** Mid-market PMO directors and program leaders (50–500 person companies) who need real portfolio governance without the bloat, cost, or undisciplined defaults of enterprise incumbents.

**Methodology framing:** primepm is also the public artifact of an agentic engineering methodology developed by a solo builder. The 90-day execution arc described in this document is itself the case study. Build cadence and design decisions will be documented as they happen.

