## 5. Out of Scope (Hard No List)

The following are explicitly excluded from the next 90 days. Resist scope creep.

- Deepening the scheduling engine (resource leveling, advanced calendar features, additional constraint types).
- Extending AHP or criteria management.
- Portfolio simulation features (DB groundwork remains; UI not prioritized).
- External system integrations (Jira, MS Project, ERP, financial systems).
- SOC2, ISO 27001, or other formal compliance certifications.
- Enterprise SSO beyond Google OAuth (SAML, Microsoft, Okta).
- Native task management / Kanban competing with Jira/Asana/Linear.
- Document collaboration / wiki features.
- Mobile native apps (responsive web is sufficient).
- AI-assisted narrative generation for status reports.
- Predictive risk models (manual entry is the baseline).
- White-label or multi-language support.

Any feature request not on the Phase 1–3 list and not on the explicit Out of Scope list defaults to **deferred**, not "considered."

