## 6. Buyer & Audience

**Primary economic buyer:** PMO Director / Program Management Office leadership at mid-market companies (50–500 employees).

**Secondary buyer / decision influencer:** CFO, COO, or Head of Strategy concerned about capital allocation discipline and project portfolio ROI.

**Daily user:** Project Managers (acknowledged friction — see Risk section).

**Vertical focus for first 12 months:** Capital-intensive, regulated, or program-heavy mid-market — candidate verticals include construction, engineering services, pharma/biotech, infrastructure, financial services. Avoid horizontal generic positioning. Pick 1–2 verticals after Phase 2 user conversations inform the choice.

**Geographic focus:** Initially open. Sales motion implications deferred until first 5 design partners identified.

