## 8. Risks & Open Questions

**Strategic risks:**
- **PM hostility risk:** PMs are the daily user but not the buyer. Governance features (mandatory CRs, anti-gaming detection) may generate negative PM feedback. Mitigation: design PM workflow to be efficient; do not let PM feedback derail governance commitments.
- **Audience volatility:** Builder has bounced between framings (serious product, hobby, methodology vehicle) within recent strategic conversations. Risk that this framing also drifts. Mitigation: 90-day decision point with explicit criteria.
- **Solo capacity:** 90 days is aggressive. Risk of incomplete Phase 3 delivery. Mitigation: protect Phase 1 and 2 as non-negotiable; Phase 3 features are individually shippable in priority order (CR workflow > audit trail > strategic objectives > risk register > anti-gaming).

**Open questions to resolve during execution:**
- Final vertical focus for go-to-market.
- Whether to seek 3 design partners during the build or after Phase 2 demo is ready.
- Pricing model (per-project, platform fee, tiered) — defer until end of Phase 2.
- Whether to open-source any portion (scheduling engine candidate) for methodology credibility.

