## 9. Decision Point — Day 90

By **2026-08-06** (90 days from PRD v0.2 date), the following will be evaluated:

**Engineering criteria (must-haves):**
- Baseline + tracking Gantt + actuals working on real schedule data.
- EVM metrics computing correctly with S-curve and exec dashboard rendering.
- CR workflow blocks unauthorized baseline changes.
- Strategic Objectives feature operational with at least one objective linking ≥2 projects.
- Risk Register operational with at least 5 risks across categories, surfaced on exec dashboard.

**Methodology / audience criteria (signal):**
- ≥100 newsletter subscribers or equivalent engaged audience.
- ≥3 PMO-level conversations conducted with structured notes.
- ≥1 paid signal of any kind (advisory request, paid newsletter conversion, course interest).

**Decision matrix:**

| Engineering | Audience | Action |
|---|---|---|
| ✅ Met | ✅ Met | Commit harder. Pick vertical. Begin design partner conversations. |
| ✅ Met | ❌ Not met | Methodology positioning is not landing. Reassess content strategy and audience targeting. Product remains a viable artifact. |
| ❌ Not met | ✅ Met | Engineering velocity is the bottleneck. Reassess scope and agentic engineering approach. |
| ❌ Not met | ❌ Not met | Hobby project. Continue or shelve based on personal interest, with no business pretension. |

The decision is binary at the engineering level (shipped or not), continuous at the audience level (signal strength). Document the outcome publicly regardless.

